SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 825
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Cooper Thompson, 2026
Valedictorian of Chester County High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pay tribute to
those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to academic
excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Cooper Thompson is one such exceptional student, who was recently
named Valedictorian of the 2026 graduating class at Chester County High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Mr. Thompson has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in his remarkable high school career, Cooper Thompson has earned an
exemplary 99.836 grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities,
including soccer and cross country; and
WHEREAS, his display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well for his
future success as a student at Freed-Hardeman University, where he will study science with the
goal of working in research; and
WHEREAS, Cooper Thompson's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of
pride for his parents, Chad and Sandy Thompson, his school, and his community; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Thompson's favorite pastimes include playing basketball, reading,
drinking coffee and tea, and playing guitar; this summer, he plans to attend a summer camp, go
on a ten-day mission to Costa Rica, and travel to Canada with his family to watch an F1 race;
and
SJR0825
013447
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Cooper Thompson is also a devout Christian and resolves to remain faith-
centered in everything he does; and
WHEREAS, Cooper Thompson's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the
respect, admiration, and commendation of the members of this General Assembly; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we commend and honor the 2026 Chester County
High School Valedictorian, Cooper Thompson, on his impressive academic achievement and
extend to him our best wishes for a happy, successful future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
